results.name: Fermi-Dirac analog of EKG sequence (A064413): a(1)=1; a(2)=2; for n > 2, a(n) = smallest number not already used which shares a Fermi-Dirac factor with a(n-1).
comment: Every positive integer is a unique product of distinct terms of A050376, which is called a Fermi-Dirac factorization of n.
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
